    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1848-10-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1848-10-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="75"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d75">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Bancroft</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Buchanan</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">United States Legation</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1848-10-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 19, 1848.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I send you a man of Vancouver’s Island, recently
                    published by James Wyld, geographer to the Queen. It purports to mark, by a
                    dotted line, the boundary between the United States and Great Britain. You will
                    see that this map suggests an encroachment on our rights by adopting a line far
                    to the east of the Straits of Haro. You may remember that Mr. Boyd, more than
                    two years ago, suggested to you that a design of preferring some such claims
                    existed. I inferred, from what I could learn at that time, that this design grew
                    up with the Hudson’s Bay Company, and I had no reason to suppose it favored by
                    the Colonial Secretary. * * *<seg type="margin">Mr. Bancroft continues the
                        suggestion that unjust claims may be made.</seg>
                </p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>GEORGE BANCROFT.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James Buchanan</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">Secretary
                            of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>, <hi rend="italic">D.
                            C</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
